LightRAG
LightRAG is described as a fast and simple RAG system that processes documents using graph-based retrieval.<SEP>LightRAG is described as a fast and simple Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system designed for efficient document processing and retrieval.

fast
Fast is described as a property of LightRAG.

simple
Simple is described as a property of LightRAG.

RAG
RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation.

document
Documents are mentioned as objects that LightRAG processes.

graph-based retrieval
Graph-based retrieval is described as a technique used by LightRAG.

LLM
LLM is mentioned as a model used with LightRAG.

embedding models
Embedding models are mentioned as models used with LightRAG.

local
Local is mentioned as an environmental condition where LightRAG can be run.

OpenAI API
OpenAI API is mentioned as an external service required for running LightRAG.

knowledge graphs
Knowledge graphs are mentioned as tools enhancing the accuracy of retrieval in LightRAG.

Reed Hastings
Reed Hastings is a co-founder of Netflix.

Marc Randolph
Marc Randolph is another co-founder of Netflix.

House of Cards
"House of Cards" is the first major original series produced by Netflix.

Netflix
Netflix is the corporation founded by Reed Hastings and Marc Randolph, known for introducing streaming services in 2007.

RAG System
RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation, describing how LightRAG integrates with existing LLMs and embedding models for improved data retrieval.

Knowledge Graph
Knowledge graphs are utilized by LightRAG to enhance the accuracy of retrieval operations.

Custom Reranking Function
Custom reranking functions allow for advanced filtering capabilities in the system.

RERANGAN
RERANGAN stands for Retrival-Augmented ENSure-and-Normalized Aggregation, emphasizing its role in enhancing data retrieval accuracy.

ENSURE
ENSURE stands for Efficient Normalized Aggregation Engine, highlighting its function in normalization and aggregation.<SEP>ENSURE is a specialized engine designed to streamline the normalization and aggregation phases of data processing.

Normalization
Normalization involves transforming raw data into a standardized form for easier analysis and comparison.

Aggregation
Aggregation combines individual pieces of data to create a summary or overview of the dataset.
